----- lodash -----
https://www.npmjs.com/package/lodash
https://lodash.com/
https://lodash.com/docs
Lodash makes JavaScript easier by taking the hassle out of working with arrays, numbers, objects, strings, etc
Olhar documentação, tem várias funções como _.isString e etc


----- nodemon -----
watch file: restart app when change file
https://www.npmjs.com/package/nodemon
npm install -g nodemon   //-g, global na máquina e não no projeto, consigo executar sem estar no package.json
npm install --save-dev nodemon
nodemon server.js -e js,hbs   //-e extension


----- pm2 -----
http://pm2.keymetrics.io/
Estilo o nodemon, só que mais robusto, dá pra ver consumo de memória, processador e etc.
se não intalar o pm2 de forma global, faça o seguinte
./node_modules/.bin/pm2 monit
./node_modules/.bin/pm2 status

----- yargs -----
http://yargs.js.org/
https://github.com/yargs/yargs
Facilita pegar os parâmetros passados pelo terminal (console application).
npm install yargs@4.7.1 --save

----- request -----
https://www.npmjs.com/package/request
Simplified HTTP request client.


----- axios -----
https://www.npmjs.com/package/axios
- Make XMLHttpRequests from the browser
- Make http requests from node.js
- Supports the Promise API
- Intercept request and response
- Transform request and response data
- Cancel requests
- Automatic transforms for JSON data
- Client side support for protecting against XSRF

